## COMMANDS

### `/imagine <prompt>` — Generate an image

**Basic usage:**
```
/imagine a photorealistic golden retriever puppy playing in autumn leaves
```

**With options:**
```
/imagine <prompt> [--model flash|pro] [--size 1024|2048|4096] [--ar 16:9] [--format png|jpg|webp] [--n 4] [--transparent] [--ref ./image.png] [--style ./style.png]
```

**Option reference:**

| Flag | Default | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `--model` | `flash` | `flash` = Gemini 3.1 Flash, `pro` = Gemini 3 Pro |
| `--size` | `1024` | Output resolution (512–4096px, applied to longest side) |
| `--ar` | `1:1` | Aspect ratio (e.g. `16:9`, `9:16`, `3:2`, `21:9`) |
| `--format` | `png` | Output format: `png`, `jpg`, `webp`, `avif` |
| `--n` | `1` | Number of variants to generate (1–8) |
| `--transparent` | false | Remove background, output PNG with alpha channel |
| `--green-screen` | false | Replace background with broadcast green (#00b140) |
| `--ref` | — | Path or URL to reference image (composition/subject) |
| `--style` | — | Path or URL to style reference image |
| `--seed` | random | Integer seed for reproducibility |
| `--negative` | — | Comma-separated concepts to exclude |
| `--quality` | `standard` | `standard` or `hd` (pro model only) |

