## REFERENCE IMAGES

### Subject / Composition Reference (`--ref`)
Guides the model to match the composition, subject identity, or scene layout of a reference image.

```
/imagine a professional headshot --ref ./my-photo.jpg --size 1024 --ar 1:1
/imagine the same character in a forest --ref ./character.png --model pro
```

### Style Transfer (`--style`)
Applies the visual style, color grading, brush strokes, or aesthetic of a style reference image to the generated output.

```
/imagine a mountain landscape --style ./van-gogh-starry-night.jpg
/imagine a product mockup --style ./brand-guide.png --ref ./product.png
```

Combine both for maximum control:
```
/imagine a portrait of a warrior --ref ./face-ref.png --style ./oil-painting-style.png --model pro --size 2048
```

